AGENTIC-VT 1.0

[metadata]
title: The Viture Beast Is Good. But I'd Buy This Instead.
channel: @octopusinc_
source: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dr8bPgUMVj0
upload_date: 20260518
transcript_source: captions
route: text

---

[00:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I\'ve had the Viture Beast for a few months now, but I chose not to review them. See, the specs looked great on paper. Got the widest field of view in the category, impressive brightness, built-in 3° of freedom, but when I got my early unit in January, marquee'

[00:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'features like 1,200 p resolution and 120 Hz refresh were still TBD, promised in a future firmware update. So, I decided to wait until those promises were delivered'

[00:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'upon. Well, that time is now. The Beast just got its full commercial launch with a big firmware update that brings the glasses up to date, mostly. I\'ve been testing a new production unit here, and Viture even sent me the prescription'

[00:38] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'lenses because so many of you have asked me how they work in glasses like these. I\'m Jason Howell, and I love smart glasses. Viture sent me these glasses and the prescription lenses for review.'

[00:50] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'They get no say in the editorial content of this video. And if you\'re interested in picking one up, I do have a link in the description that gets you 10% off your entire order. I will earn a small amount from purchases through that link'

[01:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'at no extra cost to you, but it helps support the channel. Thank you for doing that. So, the first thing I noticed when I put these on is that the Beast looks more like a normal pair of glasses than other'

[01:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'display glasses I\'ve tried. The frames have this really nice rounded soft quality to them. They feel pretty comfortable on the face. So, if you\'re looking for relatively normal-looking display glasses, the Beast gets closer'

[01:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to that than anything else right now. $549, though. That makes the Beast some of the more expensive options in its class. So, what does that premium get you? A 58°'

[01:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'field of view, the widest available in this category. Viture actually pulled that off by moving away from the standard birdbath optics that they used in older models and building a hybrid'

[01:53] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'system that combines birdbath and waveguide technology into what they call a prismatic lens. Also, 1,250 nits of peak brightness, nine levels of electrochromic dimming,'

[02:06] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there\'s built-in microphone, of course, a front camera for 6 degrees of freedom tracking that isn\'t actually available yet. I\'ll come back to that one a little bit later, but on paper, the Beast checks a lot of boxes. The Beast\'s'

[02:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'display is really good. It\'s sharp, vivid color reproduction without being oversaturated. At 1200p, text looks clean, images pop. But honestly, the jump from 1080p to 1200p is pretty'

[02:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'subtle on video content. On smaller text, it\'s actually pretty noticeable though, especially when I pop in the prescription lenses that Viture sent me. I will honestly take the extra'

[02:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'resolution every time, uh but just don\'t expect a dramatic leap. 120 Hz definitely is something that you\'ll notice, scrolling is smoother, and once you\'ve used it at 120 Hz, going back to 60 Hz, as usual, feels'

[02:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty sluggish. And the electrochromic dimming is the best implementation I\'ve tested. When you\'re looking at the display, everything around it just dims to whatever level that you\'ve set. When'

[03:09] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'you look away from the display area and the dimming releases, then you can see the room again, but it\'s very natural, it\'s automatic. I actually sat outside in direct sunlight and had no issues seeing the content on the display. They'

[03:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really nailed it. Now, inside the display, you get five screen size options from small to ultra large, plus a separate screen distance control that simulates how far away the display sits in space. Being able to position a'

[03:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'virtual monitor at a natural desk distance instead of having this big floating screen with no spatial context, that\'s the kind of fine-tuning that really makes the experience pretty awesome. One thing I really noticed'

[03:48] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'though is that when you bump or tap the displays as you will do regularly, the display has this like wobbly kind of water ripple quality to it. And when you\'re moving your head around and'

[04:00] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'there\'s dense text on the screen, the text kind of smears while you\'re in motion and then once you stop it sharpens. These two issues might be related. My guess is that the hybrid optics are more'

[04:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'sensitive to physical movement than a simpler bird bath setup. It\'s not going to ruin your viewing experience. It certainly didn\'t mine, but when you\'re putting them on, you\'re adjusting the fit, or you\'re reading text while you\'re'

[04:24] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'moving your head around, you\'re going to see it. Now next up, I want to talk about prescription lenses because so many of you have asked me about this. But first, if you\'re enjoying this video and videos like it, please give the channel a subscribe so you don\'t miss'

[04:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'future content like it. And thank you. So look, I wear glasses and when I\'m not wearing glasses, I\'m wearing contacts, kind of like right now. And one of the questions I get most about display glasses and the reviews I\'ve done is,'

[04:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'what do you do if you need vision correction? Well, I asked Vischer to send prescription lenses with my review unit and they did. Every Beast ships with a free prescription lens frame in the box. You take that frame to your'

[05:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'local optician and they cut lenses to your prescription same as regular glasses. If you don\'t want to deal with that, Vischer sells prescription lenses on their site for $79. That\'s what I'

[05:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have right here. Third-party companies like Lensology and Hans VR also make compatible lenses. And installation is pretty straightforward. You just pop off the nose guard, slide the lens frame into place, snap the nose guard back on,'

[05:28] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it locks it into place, and then removal is the opposite. It\'s pretty easy as well. Now with those installed and putting the glasses on my face, everything looks super sharp. And this is a very fresh prescription, by the'

[05:40] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'way. Prescription spot-on. Like [snorts] I mentioned, I actually noticed the 1200 P resolution improvement more with the prescription lenses in, particularly on text. The prescription option is legit.'

[05:52] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Pretty awesome to have that. One thing though, if you switch between contacts and glasses like I do, there\'s no good place to store these lenses when they\'re out of the glasses. The packaging is'

[06:05] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'cardboard that\'s easily collapsible, and this little foam insert that won\'t survive regular use, I know that. At $79 for the lenses on top of the $549 for the glasses, a small hard case or a'

[06:18] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pouch should be included in my opinion. Now, the Beast lives up to its name because it weighs in at 88 g, is the heaviest in the category. But honestly, on my face they\'re pretty comfortable. The frame design fits well. I still'

[06:31] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'think the Beast has the most comfortable frame of the ones I\'ve tested like the ones from Rainio and Xreal. The real issue though is heat. After around 10-12 minutes, the forehead area starts'

[06:44] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'getting super warm, and by 30 minutes, I was actually getting a little sweaty up there. Hope that\'s not too much information. The glasses themselves feel fine, no real pressure or pinching, maybe a little bit, but that hot face'

[06:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'factor is the real limitation with comfort. Very noticeable. I\'d say 1 to 2 hours maybe comfortable session there, and the heat, not the weight, is really the reason why you might stop. The'

[07:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'build, by the way, like I mentioned earlier, is plastic. Hit your markets an aluminum magnesium alloy frame, which makes it feel pretty firm, but in hand it still feels like plastic. It\'s a very solid plastic for what it\'s worth. I'

[07:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'said the same thing about the Xreal and the Rainio, so it\'s just kind of like something that they all do. Now, the glasses have a lot of built-in software features that are pretty useful. Cycling between spatial anchor,'

[07:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'smooth follow, and 0° of freedom. And then there\'s side mode that pins a smaller display in the corner of your view while you see the room. Settings memory that finally remembers your'

[07:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'refresh rate and resolution between sessions. All of this works pretty well. It makes the glasses feel pretty polished from a software standpoint. Vitur also has the Space Walker app on Mac, PC, Android, and iOS, which I\'d'

[08:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'call just a bonus, definitely not a must-have. I wasn\'t entirely blown away to be honest, but I could see it maybe developing into something more useful over time. Where I have a real issue is with 3D. The 2D to 3D real-time'

[08:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'conversion requires the Space Walker app. I found it working in the gallery, but could not figure out if there was any way to apply it to like YouTube content or any other content. The XREAL'

[08:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: '1S, by the way, has 2D to 3D built right into the glasses. A couple of button presses and it works on everything passing through the display. No separate app needed. That\'s a meaningful gap. The'

[08:41] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Beast also only supports full side-by-side 3D, not half side-by-side 3D, which is way more common on YouTube, by the way. So, finding compatible 3D content takes more effort than maybe it'

[08:55] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would if they supported half SBS. I also did notice some drift at times, the display drifting down, shifting around. It\'s like it\'s trying to find its place even though you\'re standing still. At'

[09:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'one point, I looked down at my phone and then back up to find the display had wandered far off to the left. It was totally out of whack. Feedback online seems to confirm that this is a wider issue with these glasses. Hopefully, it gets tightened up with future firmware'

[09:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'updates. And audio is pretty decent, but you got to be in a quiet room. And that, by the way, it lacks low end, right? You\'re not going to get a whole lot of low end on these glasses. build relationships with these personal AI'

[09:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'companions. So, I think that they absolutely are addictive. I mean, listen And you\'re not going to close out your ambient noise. So, if you\'re watching something like entertainment or whatever, you\'re probably going to want to have a pair of wireless earbuds in'

[09:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'while you\'re using it. I mean, they have their partnership with Harman that makes the sound that is here sound pretty special, but it doesn\'t get super loud. It\'s not going to get over a lot of'

[09:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'really noisy environment. So, keep that in mind. Oh, Vitur also sent me the Pro Mobile Dock, which I can use with my Nintendo Switch. It also works with the Switch 2. Uh took a couple of tries to get video to pass through, but once it'

[10:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'was running, it played really well. Looked great. My daughter actually tried Splatoon and said it\'s like having a really big TV right in front of you, which pretty much sums it up. The dock supports, like I said, original Switch'

[10:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and Switch 2. I think also Steam Deck, if you have that. So, is the Beast worth $549? Well, the hardware is really well-built. The display quality is pretty excellent.'

[10:34] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The design looks more like real glasses than anything else in this category, in my opinion. And the software features, you know, the screen sizing, the pinning, the degrees of freedom, that electrochromic dimming, all that is'

[10:46] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'polished, really polished, and genuinely useful. But, there are some things that give me pause. That drift that I experienced, the display wobble and text smearing when you\'re moving your head'

[10:58] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'around. It\'s not a, you know, a deal-breaker, but it\'s noticeable. The heat that builds up in the forehead, the 3D story between needing Spacewalker app for 2D to 3D conversion on limited content and only supporting full SBS 3D,'

[11:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'it really falls behind what the Xreal 1S is doing right now at a significantly lower price on device. And, remember that front camera for 6 degrees of'

[11:22] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'tracking? That\'s still not enabled. Even with this big firmware update delivering on a lot of Vitur\'s earlier promises, that one remains out there with no specific timeline in sight. Now, I\'ve done full reviews of the Rayneo Air 2'

[11:35] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Pro that recently came out at $299 and the XREAL 1S at $449. And they both cost less than the Beast at $549. Now, if I had to pick one pair,'

[11:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'honestly, I\'d go with the XREAL 1S. It delivers on its promises. That 2D to 3D conversion is pretty sweet. And I didn\'t experience any drift on these glasses. It\'s equally as comfortable. It still'

[11:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'looks good on the face even though the Beast looks maybe [music] a little bit better. I\'m not saying that the Beast is a bad product, far from it. It\'s pretty awesome. Vitur is clearly pushing out firmware updates as well and working to make it better actively. And I think'

[12:12] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'that really matters. But right now, today, the XREAL 1S [music] gives me more of what I want and for less money. Hard to beat that. Now, once again, don\'t forget, if you do want to check out the Beast, my link is in the'

[12:25] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'description, 10% off. And if you want to learn more about the XREAL 1S, which I\'ve mentioned a few times in this video, I did a full review a couple of months back. That video breaks down everything about the 1S and why it became my go-to display glasses. You can'

[12:37] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'watch it right here on the channel. I\'m Jason Howell. Thank you so much for watching. I\'ll see you in the next video.'
